WEBVTT

00:01:29.530 --> 00:01:34.930
[Our Dazzling Days]

00:01:35.280 --> 00:01:37.750
[Episode 29]

00:01:40.550 --> 00:01:41.200
My gosh.

00:01:42.509 --> 00:01:43.710
Why did you come down?

00:01:45.660 --> 00:01:46.789
Didn't I tell you
to watch him for a bit longer?

00:01:46.789 --> 00:01:48.450
The actor hasn't arrived yet.

00:01:48.590 --> 00:01:49.560
I don't care.

00:01:50.280 --> 00:01:52.039
I don't care anymore. You hear me?

00:01:52.039 --> 00:01:53.920
He just nags me every single day.

00:01:53.920 --> 00:01:56.850
He's gone on about it so much
I'm even getting hungry.

00:01:57.430 --> 00:01:59.720
He's already recounting
my middle school days.

00:01:59.720 --> 00:02:01.040
He's indeed got his memories back,

00:02:01.040 --> 00:02:01.710
but I'm suffering.

00:02:01.710 --> 00:02:03.760
I just don't understand
why I'm doing this.

00:02:03.760 --> 00:02:05.610
I don't understand
what you're doing either.

00:02:05.610 --> 00:02:07.470
How did you end up eating up there?

00:02:08.080 --> 00:02:10.080
You even brought dumplings down...

00:02:10.300 --> 00:02:11.430
What's the filling?

00:02:13.520 --> 00:02:14.780
Pretty good, isn't it?

00:02:14.910 --> 00:02:15.790
Classic flavor.

00:02:15.790 --> 00:02:16.520
Pretty good.

00:02:20.970 --> 00:02:21.780
Gosh.

00:02:22.190 --> 00:02:23.850
When is Mr. Ding getting here?

00:02:26.990 --> 00:02:28.400
I asked him. He said he...

00:02:30.520 --> 00:02:32.079
He said he's...

00:02:32.640 --> 00:02:35.310
Well, I think he's just shy.

00:02:35.310 --> 00:02:36.050
He just feels embarrassed.

00:02:36.050 --> 00:02:37.910
But he claims he's just soft-hearted

00:02:37.910 --> 00:02:38.710
and worries that

00:02:38.710 --> 00:02:40.840
h-he won't be able to hold it back here.

00:02:41.470 --> 00:02:42.980
No one can possibly hold it back.

00:02:42.980 --> 00:02:43.520
I'm telling you,

00:02:43.520 --> 00:02:46.120
8 out of 10 people who came here
ended up crying.

00:02:47.520 --> 00:02:48.850
What matters now is that

00:02:49.430 --> 00:02:50.120
Chief Engineer Yan

00:02:50.120 --> 00:02:52.180
keeps talking about Mr. Ding all day.

00:02:52.520 --> 00:02:54.380
While eating noodles last night,

00:02:54.430 --> 00:02:56.760
he asked
where the hero of our factory was.

00:02:57.780 --> 00:02:58.280
So what?

00:02:58.280 --> 00:03:00.310
Does everyone have to come and cry once

00:03:00.310 --> 00:03:02.240
until it stops with someone?

00:03:02.260 --> 00:03:03.690
What else can we do?

00:03:04.840 --> 00:03:06.030
Alright. I... I'll go home

00:03:06.030 --> 00:03:07.490
and talk to Mr. Ding again.

00:03:07.650 --> 00:03:08.820
He has to come and save me.

00:03:08.820 --> 00:03:10.450
I really can't take it anymore.

00:03:10.450 --> 00:03:13.210
It's really torturing me mentally.

00:03:13.470 --> 00:03:14.870
I'm psychologically fragile too, you know?

00:03:14.870 --> 00:03:16.930
What if this makes me fall sick again?

00:03:19.090 --> 00:03:20.750
The pressure is just too much.

00:03:23.610 --> 00:03:24.740
Go get him. Hurry up.

00:03:25.400 --> 00:03:26.150
Get him now?

00:03:26.400 --> 00:03:28.000
W-What else do you want to do?

00:03:28.740 --> 00:03:29.310
Go on.

00:03:31.030 --> 00:03:32.870
Let's go. He's right up there.

00:03:32.870 --> 00:03:34.070
They're all up there.

00:03:34.630 --> 00:03:35.840
Look. I-I'm just useless, aren't I?

00:03:35.840 --> 00:03:36.710
I just got here and I already
feel like crying.

00:03:36.710 --> 00:03:38.190
So anyone who comes here
can't hold it back,

00:03:38.190 --> 00:03:38.680
huh?

00:03:42.910 --> 00:03:44.640
Mr. Ding, you're finally here.

00:03:45.150 --> 00:03:46.240
Today, you'll be the second male lead.

00:03:46.240 --> 00:03:47.350
Second male lead...

00:03:47.350 --> 00:03:48.350
Where is the restroom?

00:03:48.350 --> 00:03:48.840
Don't, don't.

00:03:48.840 --> 00:03:49.710
Mr. Ding, where are you going?

00:03:49.710 --> 00:03:51.630
Come on. You've already
changed your clothes.

00:03:51.630 --> 00:03:52.870
Are you backing out at the last minute?

00:03:52.870 --> 00:03:54.170
Back in your army days,
could you be like this?

00:03:54.170 --> 00:03:55.329
What's up there?

00:03:55.680 --> 00:03:56.680
It's the enemy's high ground.

00:03:56.680 --> 00:03:57.910
And our mission today

00:03:57.910 --> 00:03:59.079
is to take that high ground.

00:03:59.079 --> 00:04:00.280
T-T-Then you come up with me.

00:04:00.280 --> 00:04:01.080
I really can't do it anymore.

00:04:01.080 --> 00:04:02.510
I've talked my mouth dry.

00:04:02.560 --> 00:04:03.820
-I can't possibly keep up with...
-Go on up.

00:04:03.820 --> 00:04:04.750
Don't give me that.

00:04:04.750 --> 00:04:06.000
They say father and son
fight side by side.

00:04:06.000 --> 00:04:07.310
If you, the father, don't go up... No...

00:04:07.310 --> 00:04:08.710
What was that nonsense?

00:04:08.710 --> 00:04:09.610
If I, the father, go up,

00:04:09.610 --> 00:04:11.410
then how can you, the son, don't?

00:04:12.280 --> 00:04:13.680
In the back room. In here.

00:04:14.120 --> 00:04:14.710
Go in.

00:04:19.680 --> 00:04:20.269
Go on in.

00:04:20.680 --> 00:04:21.329
Chief Engineer Yan.

00:04:21.329 --> 00:04:22.330
My mentor is here.

00:04:24.040 --> 00:04:25.510
What brings you two here?

00:04:25.510 --> 00:04:26.920
Please, sit.

00:04:26.920 --> 00:04:27.650
Mentor, sit.

00:04:30.720 --> 00:04:32.240
It's been a while since we met.

00:04:32.240 --> 00:04:32.900
Yes, it has.

00:04:34.510 --> 00:04:35.909
Have you been doing well?

00:04:36.650 --> 00:04:37.200
Yeah.

00:04:38.510 --> 00:04:39.310
What's up?

00:04:41.840 --> 00:04:44.000
Well, uh... It's... It's

00:04:44.120 --> 00:04:45.270
about my mentor's blueprints.

00:04:45.270 --> 00:04:46.120
There are a few parts

00:04:46.120 --> 00:04:47.920
h-he can't quite figure out.

00:04:48.510 --> 00:04:49.159
Alright.

00:04:50.720 --> 00:04:52.180
It's just when you came in,

00:04:52.800 --> 00:04:53.730
I was a bit dazed.

00:04:54.170 --> 00:04:55.740
You look just like your father.

00:04:55.740 --> 00:04:56.860
Not really. He...

00:04:58.120 --> 00:04:59.409
His father wasn't as sturdy as him,

00:04:59.409 --> 00:05:00.870
and wasn't as tall either.

00:05:01.040 --> 00:05:02.160
You knew his father well.

00:05:02.160 --> 00:05:04.920
I remember you two joined the plant
right after each other,

00:05:04.920 --> 00:05:07.240
and you apprenticed under the same mentor.

00:05:07.240 --> 00:05:09.570
What was that old master's surname again?

00:05:10.310 --> 00:05:11.120
Master Niu.

00:05:12.510 --> 00:05:13.390
Yan.

00:05:14.240 --> 00:05:15.720
Back then, didn't you like to

00:05:15.720 --> 00:05:17.210
argue with my mentor? Right?

00:05:17.210 --> 00:05:18.870
He was always arguing with me.

00:05:18.920 --> 00:05:19.850
He was stubborn.

00:05:20.510 --> 00:05:21.920
But frankly speaking,

00:05:21.940 --> 00:05:25.040
talented people always have a temper.

00:05:25.510 --> 00:05:26.120
Not to mention anything else,

00:05:26.120 --> 00:05:28.410
just look at the apprentices he trained,
including you.

00:05:28.410 --> 00:05:30.140
Every single one is excellent.

00:05:32.110 --> 00:05:34.800
You have no idea
how your grand-mentor treated me.

00:05:34.800 --> 00:05:35.510
Just three words:

00:05:35.510 --> 00:05:36.020
rough and tough.

00:05:36.020 --> 00:05:37.240
A flurry of whirlwind kicks,

00:05:37.240 --> 00:05:38.500
and he'd kick me dizzy.

00:05:39.310 --> 00:05:40.120
He kicked me every day.

00:05:40.120 --> 00:05:42.000
But look, he kicked
an eighth-grade turner out of me.

00:05:42.000 --> 00:05:44.430
Speaking of my grand-mentor
kicking my mentor,

00:05:44.430 --> 00:05:46.510
my mentor here actually inherited it well.

00:05:46.510 --> 00:05:47.830
When he kicked me back then,

00:05:47.830 --> 00:05:48.580
not to mention whirlwind kicks,

00:05:48.580 --> 00:05:49.800
he even used roundhouse kicks.

00:05:49.800 --> 00:05:51.159
One kick would send me flying
5 or 6 meters.

00:05:51.159 --> 00:05:51.850
Five or 6 meters, you know?

00:05:51.850 --> 00:05:53.380
Three kicks and I'd be home.

00:05:53.640 --> 00:05:56.040
Roundhouse kick? Didn't seem to work well.

00:05:56.310 --> 00:05:57.310
This kid was naughty when he was little.

00:05:57.310 --> 00:05:58.450
If nothing held him down,

00:05:58.450 --> 00:06:00.250
he would have flown into the sky.

00:06:01.360 --> 00:06:02.750
Our East Chemical Plant

00:06:02.950 --> 00:06:03.810
is close-knit.

00:06:04.640 --> 00:06:05.370
It really is.

00:06:05.450 --> 00:06:07.060
We're like a family.

00:06:07.620 --> 00:06:09.280
What's that old saying again?

00:06:09.470 --> 00:06:11.440
Big hands holding small hands,

00:06:12.270 --> 00:06:14.130
one generation follows another.

00:06:14.680 --> 00:06:17.120
Look how time flies.

00:06:18.310 --> 00:06:19.570
He's already grown up—

00:06:19.680 --> 00:06:21.720
a full-fledged adult now—
and we're getting old.

00:06:21.720 --> 00:06:24.450
We can't hold their hands again
even if we want to.

00:06:32.730 --> 00:06:33.590
I'm old indeed.

00:06:36.070 --> 00:06:38.220
I don't even have the strength
to dig the ground anymore.

00:06:38.220 --> 00:06:39.260
You're not old.

00:06:40.360 --> 00:06:41.480
You're still in your prime.

00:06:41.480 --> 00:06:44.120
Besides, if you're tired,

00:06:44.430 --> 00:06:46.120
just take a rest. No worries.

00:06:46.510 --> 00:06:47.720
We've got your back.

00:06:48.000 --> 00:06:49.310
The small hands from back then

00:06:49.310 --> 00:06:51.190
have grown up too, right?

00:06:51.740 --> 00:06:54.370
We'll hold the next generation's hands.

00:06:54.470 --> 00:06:57.360
One generation following another,
we'll move forward together.

00:06:57.360 --> 00:06:59.950
There will always be people
supporting our plant.

00:06:59.950 --> 00:07:01.220
I love hearing that.

00:07:02.430 --> 00:07:04.940
Now that sounds like something
someone from our plant would say.

00:07:04.940 --> 00:07:06.200
Strong and confident.

00:07:06.830 --> 00:07:07.830
I... Well, I...

00:07:07.830 --> 00:07:08.770
I need to go to the restroom.

00:07:08.770 --> 00:07:09.430
What's wrong?

00:07:09.430 --> 00:07:10.830
I-I'll escort you there.

00:07:10.980 --> 00:07:13.310
Why would I need an escort
to the restroom?

00:07:16.450 --> 00:07:18.180
Your mentor hasn't had it easy.

00:07:19.920 --> 00:07:21.360
He's getting old now.

00:07:21.790 --> 00:07:23.720
Make sure you take good care of him.

00:07:24.870 --> 00:07:25.680
I will.

00:07:26.870 --> 00:07:27.680
He's like

00:07:30.480 --> 00:07:32.360
a father to me, you know.

00:07:32.510 --> 00:07:33.680
So please,

00:07:33.680 --> 00:07:35.510
take good care of your health too,

00:07:35.510 --> 00:07:36.640
Chief Engineer Yan.

00:08:00.160 --> 00:08:02.360
Why are you getting all teary-eyed too?

00:08:03.240 --> 00:08:04.310
You started it.

00:08:04.310 --> 00:08:05.600
I didn't start it.

00:08:06.240 --> 00:08:09.270
We just asked you to go up
and put on a little act,

00:08:09.270 --> 00:08:11.120
but you brought up all these memories.

00:08:11.120 --> 00:08:11.980
This is just...

00:08:12.260 --> 00:08:14.190
It's mainly because of your lines.

00:08:14.870 --> 00:08:16.920
They were so hard-hitting.
"Big hands holding small hands."

00:08:16.920 --> 00:08:19.850
I couldn't stand it.
Tears just came streaming down.

00:08:22.920 --> 00:08:24.270
Man, this acting.

00:08:24.850 --> 00:08:25.630
He probably didn't feel much,

00:08:25.630 --> 00:08:27.690
but we got so emotional acting it out.

00:08:30.870 --> 00:08:31.510
Let's go.

00:08:31.680 --> 00:08:33.039
Let me hold your hand for a walk.

00:08:33.039 --> 00:08:33.900
Give me a break.

00:08:35.070 --> 00:08:36.789
-Just for a while.
-Why so mushy?

00:08:36.789 --> 00:08:37.200
Piss off.

00:08:37.200 --> 00:08:38.720
Just for a bit. W-What's the big deal?

00:08:38.720 --> 00:08:39.440
Making such a fuss. Is this too mushy?

00:08:39.440 --> 00:08:41.120
I just blew my nose with this hand.

00:08:41.120 --> 00:08:41.960
Let's go.

00:08:43.669 --> 00:08:45.270
-How nice.
-Don't touch me.

00:08:57.440 --> 00:08:58.770
You're really shy, huh?

00:08:59.090 --> 00:09:00.820
Your whole face is turning red.

00:09:07.390 --> 00:09:08.110
Mr. Fan.

00:09:11.510 --> 00:09:12.200
Hello.

00:09:15.030 --> 00:09:15.840
Hello, hello.

00:09:15.840 --> 00:09:16.270
Hello.

00:09:18.030 --> 00:09:19.560
You must be Mr. Yu's friend.

00:09:20.200 --> 00:09:21.130
How impressive.

00:09:21.840 --> 00:09:23.550
Mr. Fan, you even know our Yu.

00:09:24.290 --> 00:09:25.440
Since I do business here,

00:09:25.440 --> 00:09:27.700
of course I know some local celebrities.

00:09:29.000 --> 00:09:30.800
So, bro, what do you need from me?

00:09:32.510 --> 00:09:35.390
Actually, it's nothing big.

00:09:35.570 --> 00:09:36.440
Nothing serious.

00:09:36.440 --> 00:09:37.240
It's just...

00:09:38.030 --> 00:09:40.840
I hope you go back

00:09:41.270 --> 00:09:42.530
to where you came from.

00:09:43.000 --> 00:09:46.080
Even if you want to acquire Factory No. 3,
you have to see

00:09:46.870 --> 00:09:49.510
if you're tough enough—

00:09:49.690 --> 00:09:52.290
if you're as tough as
the steel in this factory.

00:09:52.870 --> 00:09:54.200
Well, yes, I-I know

00:09:54.320 --> 00:09:56.600
it's not like I can just acquire it
simply because I want to.

00:09:56.600 --> 00:09:57.600
Since I got here,

00:09:57.600 --> 00:09:59.440
I've found that
things are indeed very complicated.

00:09:59.440 --> 00:10:00.840
So please rest assured, bro.

00:10:00.840 --> 00:10:02.640
I will definitely think it over.

00:10:02.750 --> 00:10:03.840
Even if you didn't come,

00:10:03.840 --> 00:10:04.810
I'd still think about it.

00:10:04.810 --> 00:10:07.330
And I-I-I might not
necessarily acquire it.

00:10:08.580 --> 00:10:09.310
Great.

00:10:09.600 --> 00:10:12.120
Then I hope you...
Really think it through.

00:10:12.120 --> 00:10:12.870
Definitely.

00:10:12.910 --> 00:10:14.120
Anyway,

00:10:14.630 --> 00:10:18.440
we don't want to see you

00:10:18.960 --> 00:10:20.870
in this factory again.

00:10:22.750 --> 00:10:23.320
Is that clear?

00:10:23.320 --> 00:10:25.270
Clear. Totally clear.
You definitely won't see me again.

00:10:25.270 --> 00:10:26.240
I'm smart.

00:10:26.720 --> 00:10:27.480
Thank you.

00:10:29.120 --> 00:10:30.180
Alright, alright.

00:10:36.080 --> 00:10:36.800
Hello?

00:10:36.870 --> 00:10:38.270
Mr. Xia, you seem free today.

00:10:38.270 --> 00:10:39.310
To be calling me.

00:10:39.630 --> 00:10:42.360
Eight, I need to ask you for a favor.

00:10:43.260 --> 00:10:45.570
What's wrong? Are you in trouble?

00:10:45.840 --> 00:10:48.120
I'm trying to save our factory.

00:10:48.840 --> 00:10:50.170
Can you come and help me?

00:10:50.240 --> 00:10:51.840
Sure, I'll definitely come.

00:10:53.840 --> 00:10:55.840
Although I expected you to say that,

00:10:56.240 --> 00:10:58.000
I'm still touched to hear it.

00:10:59.070 --> 00:10:59.930
Alright, Xia Lei.

00:10:59.930 --> 00:11:00.970
Don't give me that.

00:11:00.970 --> 00:11:02.900
Just wait. I'll be there tomorrow.

00:11:03.240 --> 00:11:04.100
Thanks, Eight.

00:11:08.390 --> 00:11:10.000
Wearing this uniform,

00:11:10.550 --> 00:11:11.750
with you guys around—

00:11:12.030 --> 00:11:13.750
it feels like we're back
working at the factory again.

00:11:13.750 --> 00:11:14.480
You know,

00:11:14.480 --> 00:11:15.480
seeing you youngsters

00:11:15.480 --> 00:11:17.010
in these uniforms actually

00:11:17.450 --> 00:11:19.550
reminds me of
when I went to the Personnel Department

00:11:19.550 --> 00:11:20.600
to pick you up.

00:11:21.960 --> 00:11:22.720
Yeah.

00:11:23.170 --> 00:11:24.200
Seeing you dressed like this

00:11:24.200 --> 00:11:25.380
reminds me of the first time

00:11:25.380 --> 00:11:27.080
your mentor wore this uniform.

00:11:27.080 --> 00:11:28.120
He looked really handsome.

00:11:28.120 --> 00:11:28.550
Right?

00:11:28.790 --> 00:11:30.000
None of you have seen it.

00:11:30.000 --> 00:11:31.000
He looked so sharp in it.

00:11:31.000 --> 00:11:32.550
His back was straight like a soldier's.

00:11:32.550 --> 00:11:33.790
He used to be a squad leader, after all.

00:11:33.790 --> 00:11:34.740
Of course he looked the part.

00:11:34.740 --> 00:11:37.000
It feels like the old days in the factory.

00:11:37.630 --> 00:11:38.890
We may be few in number,

00:11:39.150 --> 00:11:41.190
but you must be of one mind

00:11:41.210 --> 00:11:42.520
and work in unity.

00:11:42.750 --> 00:11:43.440
Xiaoman.

00:11:44.030 --> 00:11:45.390
You've finished dressing up?

00:11:45.390 --> 00:11:46.600
I prepared flowers for you guys.

00:11:46.600 --> 00:11:48.870
Give one to each client
when you visit them.

00:11:48.870 --> 00:11:50.870
If they're happy,
maybe they'll even help promote us.

00:11:50.870 --> 00:11:52.690
Plus, you guys will be happy
working with flowers,

00:11:52.690 --> 00:11:53.170
right?

00:11:53.600 --> 00:11:54.720
Look at how thoughtful she is.

00:11:54.720 --> 00:11:56.320
You really have a way with things.

00:11:56.320 --> 00:11:58.650
Come on. Let me say a few words.

00:11:59.530 --> 00:12:01.000
It's our first day of work.

00:12:01.030 --> 00:12:01.960
The leader's giving a speech.

00:12:01.960 --> 00:12:03.630
Listen, today

00:12:03.840 --> 00:12:05.170
is the first day we enter

00:12:05.550 --> 00:12:08.150
the field of high-end moving services.

00:12:08.410 --> 00:12:10.890
We must do this first job well

00:12:11.240 --> 00:12:12.240
and beautifully.

00:12:12.320 --> 00:12:14.790
Let's make Manyi Moving a hit.

00:12:15.240 --> 00:12:15.840
Got it!

00:12:16.390 --> 00:12:17.510
-Got it!
-Got it!

00:12:21.150 --> 00:12:23.410
Comrade Chief, please
give your instructions!

00:12:23.410 --> 00:12:24.550
Oh my, this involves me too?

00:12:24.550 --> 00:12:25.280
My goodness.

00:12:27.830 --> 00:12:28.690
Get on the road!

00:12:29.200 --> 00:12:30.400
-Yes, sir!
-Yes, sir!

00:12:33.440 --> 00:12:34.470
Let's get to work.

00:12:35.870 --> 00:12:36.600
Clean this up.

00:12:36.600 --> 00:12:37.890
Leave it by the door to take out later.

00:12:37.890 --> 00:12:38.320
Got it.

00:12:39.600 --> 00:12:40.320
Xiaoman.

00:12:40.510 --> 00:12:41.000
Yes, bro?

00:12:41.000 --> 00:12:43.720
If you're tired, take a break
and have some water.

00:12:43.720 --> 00:12:45.650
We're okay. It's just a bit of work.

00:12:45.750 --> 00:12:48.120
Bro, your house is so grand.

00:12:48.630 --> 00:12:50.890
I'd never finish in a day
without my crew.

00:12:51.310 --> 00:12:52.630
You know what, Xiaoman?

00:12:52.630 --> 00:12:53.320
This house

00:12:53.320 --> 00:12:55.390
is actually the smallest one I own.

00:12:55.470 --> 00:12:56.000
Man.

00:12:56.000 --> 00:12:57.750
I didn't dare show you the big ones.

00:12:57.750 --> 00:12:59.480
I was worried you'd be shocked.

00:13:00.270 --> 00:13:01.200
What do you think, bro?

00:13:01.200 --> 00:13:04.000
Are you satisfied with
our moving and everything?

00:13:05.360 --> 00:13:06.270
To be honest,

00:13:06.910 --> 00:13:07.870
I'm not very satisfied.

00:13:07.870 --> 00:13:08.670
What's wrong?

00:13:09.870 --> 00:13:11.440
I'm such a picky person,

00:13:11.440 --> 00:13:13.170
yet I can't find a single fault.

00:13:13.200 --> 00:13:15.000
How can I be satisfied with that?

00:13:15.510 --> 00:13:16.240
Don't worry.

00:13:16.330 --> 00:13:17.840
When we finish moving later,

00:13:17.840 --> 00:13:19.890
we'll clean up the floors and everything.

00:13:19.890 --> 00:13:21.480
We'll leave it spotless for you.

00:13:21.480 --> 00:13:22.790
Just rest assured, bro.

00:13:22.790 --> 00:13:23.440
Okay.

00:13:24.000 --> 00:13:25.200
Bro, flowers for you.

00:13:25.960 --> 00:13:27.560
These flowers are so pretty.

00:13:27.670 --> 00:13:30.320
They smell so good.
I can even smell them from here.

00:13:30.320 --> 00:13:30.920
Chunchun.

00:13:31.150 --> 00:13:31.750
Later on,

00:13:31.750 --> 00:13:33.360
I'll place an order
with your flower shop too.

00:13:33.360 --> 00:13:34.790
From now on, for my house,

00:13:35.150 --> 00:13:37.630
my parents' house, and my in-laws' house—

00:13:37.920 --> 00:13:39.750
I want you to arrange flowers
for all of them.

00:13:39.750 --> 00:13:41.840
Fill every floor to the brim.

00:13:42.150 --> 00:13:44.410
I want that "wow" factor when you walk in.

00:13:44.410 --> 00:13:46.200
This is a standing order. Got it?

00:13:46.200 --> 00:13:47.030
Sure, no problem.

00:13:47.030 --> 00:13:48.670
I'll mix up the styles for you.

00:13:48.670 --> 00:13:50.200
You're really like a kind brother to us.

00:13:50.200 --> 00:13:52.590
I've got to act like one, you know?

00:13:52.840 --> 00:13:54.000
Alright, you guys get back to work.

00:13:54.000 --> 00:13:55.150
-Okay, bro.
-I... I need to use the restroom.

00:13:55.150 --> 00:13:56.080
Sure, sure.

00:13:58.030 --> 00:13:59.280
Always say "thank you, bro," right?

00:13:59.280 --> 00:14:01.000
It's never wrong to show respect
to our clients.

00:14:01.000 --> 00:14:01.440
Got it.

00:14:01.550 --> 00:14:03.000
Let me hear you say "thank you, bro."

00:14:03.000 --> 00:14:03.860
Thank you, bro.

00:14:04.630 --> 00:14:05.750
Sweeter would be better.

00:14:05.750 --> 00:14:06.440
Thank you, bro.

00:14:06.440 --> 00:14:07.030
Just like that. Just like that.

00:14:07.030 --> 00:14:07.760
Not bad, huh?

00:14:07.840 --> 00:14:08.840
I'll go help Nana then.

00:14:08.840 --> 00:14:09.200
Okay.

00:14:38.870 --> 00:14:39.790
Mom. Mom.

00:14:43.070 --> 00:14:43.550
Mom.

00:14:48.120 --> 00:14:48.670
Sweetie.

00:14:49.870 --> 00:14:51.360
It's just like before—

00:14:51.480 --> 00:14:53.480
exactly like when he was young.

00:14:54.960 --> 00:14:56.930
He's working there just fine.

00:14:56.960 --> 00:14:59.270
How does he look like a sick person?

00:14:59.910 --> 00:15:01.670
He's not sick at all.

00:15:03.510 --> 00:15:04.970
He'll get better. He will.

00:15:06.290 --> 00:15:07.130
You know what?

00:15:07.960 --> 00:15:09.320
Whenever he worked overtime
when he were young,

00:15:09.320 --> 00:15:10.450
I'd wait right here.

00:15:11.000 --> 00:15:12.120
I didn't want to
get in the way of his work,

00:15:12.120 --> 00:15:13.450
so I didn't dare to go in.

00:15:13.630 --> 00:15:15.960
He wouldn't even lift his head.

00:15:16.790 --> 00:15:17.960
He couldn't hear anything,

00:15:17.960 --> 00:15:19.620
and he couldn't see anything.

00:15:21.150 --> 00:15:22.870
How did he get sick?

00:15:27.370 --> 00:15:29.320
Sweetie, how did he end up sick?

00:15:37.910 --> 00:15:40.080
Don't cry in front of Dad, alright?

00:15:41.340 --> 00:15:41.910
Okay.

00:15:43.750 --> 00:15:45.210
I'll go bring him the food.

00:15:45.850 --> 00:15:46.910
Bring him the food.

00:15:58.600 --> 00:16:00.600
Yan, time to eat.

00:16:01.550 --> 00:16:02.320
You're here.

00:16:02.390 --> 00:16:03.870
I brought you some food.

00:16:05.480 --> 00:16:07.280
Thanks for the trouble, my dear.

00:16:07.390 --> 00:16:08.990
Guess what dishes I brought.

00:16:09.870 --> 00:16:10.750
Braised pork.

00:16:11.240 --> 00:16:11.960
And?

00:16:12.130 --> 00:16:12.790
What's this?

00:16:12.790 --> 00:16:13.480
Green beans.

00:16:13.480 --> 00:16:15.000
Green beans. Good.

00:16:16.600 --> 00:16:17.360
Great.

00:16:17.630 --> 00:16:19.320
Our Yan works so hard.

00:16:19.320 --> 00:16:20.910
You've worked hard too, my dear.

00:16:20.910 --> 00:16:21.770
Have you eaten?

00:16:22.000 --> 00:16:22.630
Not yet.

00:16:22.630 --> 00:16:23.870
-Let's eat together then.
-I'll eat with you.

00:16:23.870 --> 00:16:24.790
Alright.

00:16:26.680 --> 00:16:28.340
The sofa over there is too low.

00:16:29.080 --> 00:16:31.960
Let's just make do here.

00:16:35.200 --> 00:16:38.360
Well, the weather lately

00:16:38.910 --> 00:16:39.640
has been dry.

00:16:40.840 --> 00:16:42.230
Next time you bring me food,

00:16:42.230 --> 00:16:43.350
make me some soup.

00:16:43.550 --> 00:16:45.270
There's going to be a next time?

00:16:45.270 --> 00:16:46.870
You'll work overtime again?

00:16:48.240 --> 00:16:49.670
Of course I have to.

00:16:49.690 --> 00:16:52.090
Who else will do all the work
in the factory?

00:16:52.320 --> 00:16:53.240
I'm telling you,

00:16:53.240 --> 00:16:55.120
you can't rely on those young people.

00:16:55.120 --> 00:16:56.870
They can't do without you.

00:17:28.349 --> 00:17:29.910
Hello? Is this the police?

00:17:31.440 --> 00:17:32.350
Was it 4 people

00:17:32.350 --> 00:17:33.160
or 5?

00:17:34.270 --> 00:17:35.830
Maybe 6 or 7?

00:17:36.270 --> 00:17:38.670
It was pitch black.
I couldn't see clearly.

00:17:39.050 --> 00:17:40.480
There were quite a few people anyway.

00:17:40.480 --> 00:17:41.440
Was anyone hurt?

00:17:41.750 --> 00:17:42.400
No one was hurt.

00:17:42.400 --> 00:17:44.400
I was the only one on duty yesterday.

00:17:45.750 --> 00:17:46.790
Director, do this.

00:17:46.790 --> 00:17:48.960
Calculate the losses

00:17:48.960 --> 00:17:50.100
and report back to us.

00:17:50.100 --> 00:17:51.170
The National Security Brigade

00:17:51.170 --> 00:17:52.170
is on their way.

00:17:52.200 --> 00:17:53.590
They need to gather some materials.

00:17:53.590 --> 00:17:55.180
That way, when determining liability,

00:17:55.180 --> 00:17:56.110
there will be a basis for it.

00:17:56.110 --> 00:17:56.920
Okay.

00:17:59.120 --> 00:17:59.880
Mr. Song.

00:18:01.830 --> 00:18:03.880
Why didn't you tell me
what happened yesterday?

00:18:03.880 --> 00:18:05.680
What's the point of telling you?

00:18:06.300 --> 00:18:08.100
Until this factory is acquired,

00:18:08.310 --> 00:18:10.510
it's still the factory's own business.

00:18:10.790 --> 00:18:11.450
Who is that?

00:18:11.790 --> 00:18:12.510
Xia Lei.

00:18:12.680 --> 00:18:13.810
One of our factory kids.

00:18:13.810 --> 00:18:14.870
He's back this time

00:18:15.070 --> 00:18:17.000
to discuss acquiring the factory.

00:18:21.590 --> 00:18:22.520
Hello, Officer.

00:18:25.350 --> 00:18:28.550
Do you think this incident
is related to the acquisition?

00:18:29.350 --> 00:18:31.400
Officer, here's what I think.

00:18:31.400 --> 00:18:33.070
There's a man named Yu Qiangbei.

00:18:33.070 --> 00:18:34.790
He's a businessman from Tiecheng.

00:18:34.790 --> 00:18:36.590
He hired someone to threaten me before.

00:18:36.590 --> 00:18:37.720
He sent me a message,

00:18:38.110 --> 00:18:41.040
asking me to give up the acquisition of
Factory No. 3.

00:18:41.220 --> 00:18:42.590
But I... I don't have any evidence.

00:18:42.590 --> 00:18:44.050
T-This is mere suspicion.

00:18:46.010 --> 00:18:47.350
Thank you for the information.

00:18:47.350 --> 00:18:49.550
We'll investigate as soon as possible.

00:18:50.330 --> 00:18:51.700
Director, let's leave it at that for now.

00:18:51.700 --> 00:18:52.660
We're heading out.

00:18:52.660 --> 00:18:53.790
If anything comes up later,

00:18:53.790 --> 00:18:55.000
contact us immediately.

00:18:55.000 --> 00:18:56.060
Alright, alright.

00:18:57.140 --> 00:18:58.750
Thanks for your help, Captain Feng.

00:18:58.750 --> 00:18:59.710
Take care. Here.

00:19:02.030 --> 00:19:02.750
Take care.

00:19:04.920 --> 00:19:06.450
Yan... Chief Engineer Yan?

00:19:07.240 --> 00:19:08.590
Mr. Yan, why are you here?

00:19:08.590 --> 00:19:10.920
Something happened. How could I not come?

00:19:11.350 --> 00:19:12.030
Mr. Song is over there.

00:19:12.030 --> 00:19:12.890
What happened?

00:19:13.030 --> 00:19:14.680
You can't go in. Entry is forbidden,
Chief Engineer Yan.

00:19:14.680 --> 00:19:15.590
Come... Come over here.

00:19:15.590 --> 00:19:16.450
Look from here.

00:19:16.480 --> 00:19:17.140
Mr. Zhuang.

00:19:18.250 --> 00:19:19.480
Why did you bring Mr. Yan here?

00:19:19.480 --> 00:19:20.590
Don't you know the condition of his brain?

00:19:20.590 --> 00:19:22.200
No one could stop him.

00:19:22.590 --> 00:19:23.590
The equipment

00:19:23.720 --> 00:19:24.720
is his life.

00:19:25.410 --> 00:19:26.550
He forgets things he can afford to forget,

00:19:26.550 --> 00:19:29.480
but remembers everything
he can't afford to forget.

00:19:38.150 --> 00:19:41.630
Those vandals were obviously
a bunch of idiots—complete amateurs.

00:19:41.630 --> 00:19:42.630
Look at the equipment they smashed—

00:19:42.630 --> 00:19:45.030
they didn't even know
where the crucial parts are.

00:19:45.030 --> 00:19:45.920
No problem.

00:19:46.310 --> 00:19:48.140
It's just a small issue.
I'll have it fixed in no time.

00:19:48.140 --> 00:19:49.440
Come on. Let's get to work.

00:19:49.440 --> 00:19:50.720
Chief Engineer Yan, wait.

00:19:50.720 --> 00:19:52.240
We have to wait for
the National Security Brigade to arrive.

00:19:52.240 --> 00:19:55.400
We can only start working
after they finish inspecting the scene.

00:19:55.400 --> 00:19:55.960
Alright.

00:19:56.680 --> 00:19:58.470
Then let's go get ready.

00:19:58.680 --> 00:19:59.400
-Okay, let's go.
-Alright?

00:19:59.400 --> 00:20:00.030
Grab the tools

00:20:00.030 --> 00:20:00.770
and prepare the parts.

00:20:00.770 --> 00:20:02.170
Let's go. Let's get to it.

00:20:03.910 --> 00:20:04.500
Lei.

00:20:25.030 --> 00:20:26.360
What are you doing here?

00:20:27.160 --> 00:20:28.270
Why can't I be here?

00:20:29.190 --> 00:20:30.920
Can't I check on my competitor?

00:20:32.790 --> 00:20:33.650
Who smashed it?

00:20:35.480 --> 00:20:36.350
You don't know?

00:20:36.770 --> 00:20:38.050
Of course I don't.

00:20:39.400 --> 00:20:40.800
I never use dirty tricks,

00:20:41.240 --> 00:20:42.570
let alone break the law.

00:20:45.080 --> 00:20:47.350
Kong Peng is already under
internal investigation by Fenlier.

00:20:47.350 --> 00:20:48.700
Why would you still want to
be tied to him?

00:20:48.700 --> 00:20:50.480
Why not partner with me instead?

00:20:50.480 --> 00:20:52.610
We can acquire Factory No. 3 properly.

00:20:53.640 --> 00:20:55.040
I know he won't last long.

00:20:55.720 --> 00:20:56.720
But did you resign

00:20:56.880 --> 00:20:58.140
just for this factory?

00:20:58.330 --> 00:21:00.480
Yes, I plan to acquire it.

00:21:02.240 --> 00:21:03.440
Do you have the money?

00:21:04.000 --> 00:21:05.200
Do you have a partner?

00:21:05.650 --> 00:21:07.400
Trying to acquire it without these—

00:21:07.400 --> 00:21:08.830
how can you compete with Fenlier?

00:21:08.830 --> 00:21:11.090
I have a share in the equity resale money.

00:21:11.100 --> 00:21:12.760
When do you plan to pay me back?

00:21:13.030 --> 00:21:14.830
Alright, alright, don't change
the subject.

00:21:14.830 --> 00:21:16.030
Even if I pay you back,

00:21:16.200 --> 00:21:18.590
other factories of the same type
have better connections

00:21:18.590 --> 00:21:19.440
and newer equipment than you.

00:21:19.440 --> 00:21:21.040
How can you compete? Tell me.

00:21:21.360 --> 00:21:21.990
I know.

00:21:22.510 --> 00:21:24.790
I just want to
change this factory completely

00:21:24.790 --> 00:21:26.450
and transform it thoroughly.

00:21:26.750 --> 00:21:28.450
I'll introduce advanced technology

00:21:28.450 --> 00:21:30.200
and optimize the production process.

00:21:30.200 --> 00:21:32.600
I want to give this factory
a brand new look.

00:21:32.750 --> 00:21:35.550
Okay. Let me ask you
a presumptuous question then.

00:21:35.790 --> 00:21:38.070
How will you transform it? Tell me.

00:21:38.720 --> 00:21:41.780
I plan to produce electrolytes
for lithium batteries.

00:21:46.480 --> 00:21:48.340
Mr. Zhuang, what brings you here?

00:21:48.510 --> 00:21:49.160
Xiaodan.

00:21:49.680 --> 00:21:51.090
I'm here to see your father.

00:21:51.090 --> 00:21:52.480
Why do you want to see me?

00:21:54.510 --> 00:21:56.200
Did something happen to the equipment?

00:21:56.200 --> 00:21:57.790
No, I'm no longer

00:21:57.790 --> 00:21:59.110
in charge of the equipment.

00:21:59.110 --> 00:22:00.200
If you're not in charge, then who is?

00:22:00.200 --> 00:22:00.960
Me?

00:22:01.680 --> 00:22:02.920
I'm here to tell you

00:22:03.110 --> 00:22:04.240
that I'm retiring.

00:22:06.830 --> 00:22:07.830
You're retiring?

00:22:09.000 --> 00:22:09.860
How old are you?

00:22:09.860 --> 00:22:11.110
I've reached the age.

00:22:11.240 --> 00:22:12.840
I'm one month older than you.

00:22:13.000 --> 00:22:13.830
Next month,

00:22:13.920 --> 00:22:15.520
it'll be your turn to retire.

00:22:20.000 --> 00:22:20.590
Wait...

00:22:21.460 --> 00:22:23.150
I... I have to retire too?

00:22:23.170 --> 00:22:24.400
Look. Does the leadership

00:22:24.400 --> 00:22:26.880
get special privileges or what?

00:22:27.200 --> 00:22:28.530
You also need to retire.

00:22:29.630 --> 00:22:31.090
No privileges, of course.

00:22:31.400 --> 00:22:32.400
Come on, sit down.

00:22:33.920 --> 00:22:36.200
How come we're retiring just like that?

00:22:37.480 --> 00:22:39.590
Time flies way too fast.

00:22:40.680 --> 00:22:42.010
It's been over 40 years.

00:22:42.480 --> 00:22:43.880
It's time to take a break.

00:22:44.400 --> 00:22:45.680
Just like that?

00:22:45.920 --> 00:22:48.590
If we rest, who will do the work
at the factory?

00:22:48.960 --> 00:22:49.920
Someone will.

00:22:50.200 --> 00:22:52.110
We shouldn't worry about that.

00:22:52.400 --> 00:22:53.200
After you retire,

00:22:53.200 --> 00:22:54.830
just rest well at home

00:22:55.000 --> 00:22:56.400
and spend more time with your kid—

00:22:56.400 --> 00:22:57.160
Xiaodan.

00:22:57.720 --> 00:22:59.240
What you said is nonsense.

00:22:59.470 --> 00:23:00.550
How can I not worry?

00:23:00.830 --> 00:23:01.790
Among the people under us—

00:23:01.790 --> 00:23:02.790
those apprentices—

00:23:02.790 --> 00:23:03.920
who can take over?

00:23:04.640 --> 00:23:07.160
You just retire and wash your hands of it,

00:23:07.480 --> 00:23:08.590
but what about the factory?

00:23:08.590 --> 00:23:09.240
Dad.

00:23:10.000 --> 00:23:11.240
That's not what he meant.

00:23:11.240 --> 00:23:12.960
No, that's exactly what he meant.

00:23:12.960 --> 00:23:14.070
Look at him. When he spoke of retirement,

00:23:14.070 --> 00:23:15.090
he'd go "I'm retiring,"

00:23:15.090 --> 00:23:15.960
looking so happy

00:23:15.960 --> 00:23:17.480
like he found money on the street.

00:23:17.480 --> 00:23:18.210
Yan Wenyuan.

00:23:18.880 --> 00:23:20.400
How can you talk like that?

00:23:20.590 --> 00:23:22.030
Do I look happy to you?

00:23:22.510 --> 00:23:24.910
Don't I worry about the work
at the factory?

00:23:25.110 --> 00:23:27.920
Don't I worry about
those apprentices in the workshop?

00:23:27.920 --> 00:23:29.460
Talking about finding money on the street.

00:23:29.460 --> 00:23:31.720
Even if our company asks me
to work for free,

00:23:31.720 --> 00:23:32.430
I'd do it.

00:23:33.240 --> 00:23:34.370
I love hearing that.

00:23:34.510 --> 00:23:35.200
Don't get agitated.

00:23:35.200 --> 00:23:36.600
I'll pour you some water.

00:23:39.000 --> 00:23:39.680
Uncle.

00:23:40.510 --> 00:23:41.640
This is an act. Remember?

00:23:41.640 --> 00:23:42.590
Keep acting.

00:23:45.200 --> 00:23:46.590
I'm not acting with your dad.

00:23:46.590 --> 00:23:48.120
I'm only telling the truth.

00:23:49.140 --> 00:23:50.860
Back when I retired,

00:23:52.030 --> 00:23:53.400
it was really hard, you know?

00:23:53.400 --> 00:23:54.550
Stuck at home alone,

00:23:54.990 --> 00:23:56.310
thinking about work at the factory—

00:23:56.310 --> 00:23:59.200
I had energy but nowhere to use it.
It was suffocating.

00:23:59.200 --> 00:24:00.530
It's been over 40 years,

00:24:00.550 --> 00:24:02.000
yet I couldn't forget it.

00:24:05.740 --> 00:24:07.160
If it weren't for my son...

00:24:07.160 --> 00:24:07.880
Mr. Zhuang,

00:24:08.000 --> 00:24:10.660
didn't you come today
to remind my dad to retire?

00:24:15.760 --> 00:24:17.000
Look at my temper.

00:24:17.310 --> 00:24:19.030
I even forgot why I came here.

00:24:20.070 --> 00:24:21.330
I can't put on this act.

00:24:22.160 --> 00:24:22.890
I can't do it.

00:24:23.270 --> 00:24:24.000
I'm leaving.

00:24:24.370 --> 00:24:25.410
Act? Act what?

00:24:25.920 --> 00:24:26.840
Where are you going?

00:24:26.840 --> 00:24:27.500
He... He...

00:24:28.120 --> 00:24:29.780
You pissed him off, so he left.

00:24:31.670 --> 00:24:32.220
My fault.

00:24:34.720 --> 00:24:35.790
What's wrong, Dad?

00:24:39.550 --> 00:24:40.590
Why are you crying?

00:24:40.590 --> 00:24:43.270
It's all your fault,
making me put on that retirement act.

00:24:43.270 --> 00:24:45.070
Do you know how hard it was for me?

00:24:45.350 --> 00:24:47.550
Wasn't that to help Chief Engineer Yan?

00:24:48.000 --> 00:24:49.600
You know, for a second there,

00:24:49.960 --> 00:24:51.880
I really felt like
I was back on the day I retired.

00:24:51.880 --> 00:24:54.550
See? That's the power of drama.

00:24:54.960 --> 00:24:57.090
Get out of here with your instigating.

00:24:57.110 --> 00:24:58.310
I was supposed to heal him,

00:24:58.310 --> 00:24:59.910
but he ended up infecting me.

00:25:00.880 --> 00:25:02.350
Our factory is so great.

00:25:02.790 --> 00:25:04.310
Why did I ever retire?

00:25:05.310 --> 00:25:06.310
Dad, look at you.

00:25:06.330 --> 00:25:08.660
These old-timers at East Chemical Plant—

00:25:09.680 --> 00:25:11.810
every single one of them is top-notch.

00:25:26.590 --> 00:25:27.200
Dad.

00:25:28.640 --> 00:25:30.300
You love East Chemical Plant,

00:25:30.790 --> 00:25:32.000
and so does he.

00:25:35.790 --> 00:25:37.110
Retire...

00:25:39.880 --> 00:25:41.680
How is it time to retire already?

00:25:45.720 --> 00:25:47.050
There's one month left.

00:25:51.950 --> 00:25:53.540
Yan, what are you doing?

00:25:54.400 --> 00:25:56.550
I thought Xiaodan was coming
to bring me food.

00:25:56.550 --> 00:25:58.000
You're about to retire.

00:25:58.400 --> 00:26:01.200
I have to take the chance
to come visit you more.

00:26:01.280 --> 00:26:02.940
I won't have the chance later.

00:26:04.160 --> 00:26:05.920
You've really put up with a lot

00:26:05.920 --> 00:26:07.580
being with me all these years.

00:26:08.200 --> 00:26:10.240
Back then, you didn't
listen to your mother

00:26:10.240 --> 00:26:12.900
and insisted on coming to the Northeast
with me.

00:26:13.200 --> 00:26:14.130
And once we came,

00:26:16.720 --> 00:26:18.200
it was for life.

00:26:19.750 --> 00:26:20.640
I've been

00:26:21.240 --> 00:26:22.720
busy all my life,

00:26:22.920 --> 00:26:24.920
and I failed to take good care of you.

00:26:24.960 --> 00:26:26.400
I'm really sorry.

00:26:27.200 --> 00:26:29.720
Don't be sorry, Yan.

00:26:30.400 --> 00:26:31.830
I have so many friends.

00:26:32.400 --> 00:26:35.080
If I don't eat sauerkraut dumplings
for a week,

00:26:35.110 --> 00:26:36.000
I crave them.

00:26:42.340 --> 00:26:43.660
Sometimes after work,

00:26:45.310 --> 00:26:46.770
when the factory is empty,

00:26:47.960 --> 00:26:49.680
I like to sit here alone.

00:26:52.440 --> 00:26:53.480
I think to myself:

00:26:56.830 --> 00:26:58.740
what have I done with my life,

00:27:05.710 --> 00:27:07.840
and what have I left for this factory?

00:27:12.000 --> 00:27:12.790
You see?

00:27:16.110 --> 00:27:16.910
This bunch...

00:27:18.680 --> 00:27:21.080
This bunch of equipment was designed
by me.

00:27:22.030 --> 00:27:23.830
This is what I'm leaving behind.

00:27:25.300 --> 00:27:26.760
Do you think it's worth it?

00:27:27.640 --> 00:27:28.700
It's worth it, Yan.

00:27:43.680 --> 00:27:44.270
Lei.

00:27:47.350 --> 00:27:48.030
Zhigang?

00:27:48.200 --> 00:27:49.480
It's been so many years.

00:27:49.480 --> 00:27:50.940
I heard you've made it big,

00:27:51.160 --> 00:27:51.830
kid.

00:27:52.480 --> 00:27:53.550
I wanted to come see you,

00:27:53.550 --> 00:27:54.790
but I didn't know where your home is,

00:27:54.790 --> 00:27:56.320
so I had to wait for you here.

00:27:58.510 --> 00:27:59.680
What did you come to see me for?

00:27:59.680 --> 00:28:00.510
It's been so long.

00:28:00.510 --> 00:28:02.970
Aren't you going to invite me up
for some tea?

00:28:03.790 --> 00:28:04.320
This way.

00:28:06.400 --> 00:28:07.240
What a coincidence.

00:28:07.240 --> 00:28:08.240
I took a taxi here,

00:28:08.470 --> 00:28:10.200
and the driver was your father.

00:28:12.350 --> 00:28:13.750
Just like driving a taxi,

00:28:13.920 --> 00:28:15.920
it's really not safe being a driver.

00:28:16.030 --> 00:28:17.400
You should go back and talk to him.

00:28:17.400 --> 00:28:18.660
Tell him to be careful.

00:28:19.160 --> 00:28:20.360
What do you mean by that?

00:28:20.360 --> 00:28:21.600
What could I mean?

00:28:24.020 --> 00:28:26.480
It's about the acquisition of
Factory No. 3.

00:28:27.000 --> 00:28:28.330
You have so much money.

00:28:28.790 --> 00:28:30.840
Why don't you just buy a couple of
apartments in Shanghai?

00:28:30.840 --> 00:28:32.640
Why would you want to live in this dump?

00:28:32.640 --> 00:28:34.510
Wouldn't it be nice
to show some filial piety?

00:28:34.510 --> 00:28:35.160
True.

00:28:35.680 --> 00:28:37.110
As their filial son,

00:28:37.130 --> 00:28:38.930
I should show some filial piety.

00:28:40.160 --> 00:28:41.510
But I haven't done anything

00:28:41.510 --> 00:28:42.920
wicked, have I?

00:28:47.680 --> 00:28:49.140
Let me tell you something.

00:28:49.310 --> 00:28:51.840
Mr. Fan from the south
has already pulled out.

00:28:51.960 --> 00:28:53.360
You're the only one left.

00:28:54.110 --> 00:28:55.720
Yu has been trying to
go after you all this time.

00:28:55.720 --> 00:28:56.850
Do you have any idea?

00:28:57.720 --> 00:28:59.110
I've been holding him back for you.

00:28:59.110 --> 00:29:01.400
I watched you grow up.

00:29:01.510 --> 00:29:02.880
You're like a younger brother to me.

00:29:02.880 --> 00:29:05.140
Drop the idea of acquiring Factory No. 3.

00:29:05.160 --> 00:29:06.510
Think about yourself,

00:29:06.880 --> 00:29:08.440
and think about your parents,

00:29:08.440 --> 00:29:09.240
okay?

00:29:15.920 --> 00:29:17.450
I've been thinking lately,

00:29:18.270 --> 00:29:21.130
was your struggle to save
Jiangnan Machinery Plant

00:29:21.830 --> 00:29:23.880
even harder than mine?

00:29:25.920 --> 00:29:26.960
Jiangnan Machinery Plant

00:29:26.960 --> 00:29:28.820
has nothing to do with me anymore.

00:29:28.920 --> 00:29:29.920
Then in your eyes,

00:29:29.920 --> 00:29:31.720
what does Factory No. 3 mean now?

00:29:33.000 --> 00:29:34.930
If it can be acquired and put to use,

00:29:35.000 --> 00:29:35.880
it can make money;

00:29:35.880 --> 00:29:38.280
otherwise, it's just a pile of
scrap metal.

00:29:39.070 --> 00:29:40.250
To investors,

00:29:40.280 --> 00:29:42.000
it's just a juicy piece of meat.

00:29:42.000 --> 00:29:43.200
But to me,

00:29:43.480 --> 00:29:44.350
this is my home.

00:29:46.830 --> 00:29:48.000
I always believed that

00:29:48.000 --> 00:29:50.920
since you gave up everything
for Jiangnan Machinery Plant back then,

00:29:50.920 --> 00:29:51.720
you'd be able to understand

00:29:51.720 --> 00:29:53.580
how I feel about Factory No. 3 now.

00:29:54.030 --> 00:29:56.590
But you don't understand the feeling of
working so hard

00:29:56.590 --> 00:29:58.520
only to end up with nothing, do you?

00:30:00.240 --> 00:30:02.000
I really didn't understand you back then.

00:30:02.000 --> 00:30:04.330
But now that it's my turn,
I finally get it.

00:30:04.640 --> 00:30:06.300
Even if there's only
a one-in-a-million chance,

00:30:06.300 --> 00:30:07.500
I have to fight for it.

00:30:08.680 --> 00:30:10.270
I can't watch this place

00:30:10.270 --> 00:30:11.870
become a pile of scrap metal.

00:30:12.400 --> 00:30:14.060
I hope you can come and help me.

00:30:17.880 --> 00:30:18.590
How?

00:30:18.950 --> 00:30:20.740
Your dream is to give up money,

00:30:21.040 --> 00:30:22.700
but my dream is exactly money.

00:30:23.110 --> 00:30:23.910
Lei.

00:30:25.110 --> 00:30:27.110
You really are a risk-taking idealist.

00:30:27.110 --> 00:30:29.310
I admit you have ability and courage.

00:30:30.350 --> 00:30:31.830
But are you sure that
the two of us together

00:30:31.830 --> 00:30:33.360
can fight against capital?

00:30:35.520 --> 00:30:37.040
I know this is a gamble.

00:30:37.900 --> 00:30:39.530
No adventure, no success.

00:30:43.590 --> 00:30:45.450
Will you take this gamble with me?

00:30:51.720 --> 00:30:52.780
I'm a businessman.

00:30:53.160 --> 00:30:54.560
I'm trying to make money.

00:30:54.590 --> 00:30:55.720
I'm not a gambler.

00:30:56.420 --> 00:31:00.450
Besides, Factory No. 3
is too small a bargaining chip.

00:31:05.720 --> 00:31:06.270
Dad, Mom.

00:31:06.270 --> 00:31:06.920
You're here.

00:31:06.920 --> 00:31:07.580
We're here.

00:31:08.680 --> 00:31:09.270
Hello.

00:31:09.920 --> 00:31:11.160
This is Fan Weijie,

00:31:11.160 --> 00:31:12.160
my university senior,

00:31:12.160 --> 00:31:13.550
here to revitalize Factory No. 3 as well.

00:31:13.550 --> 00:31:14.550
Hello, young man.

00:31:14.960 --> 00:31:16.510
-Hello, Mr. and Mrs. Xia.
-Welcome, welcome.

00:31:16.510 --> 00:31:17.930
-Come on, have a seat.
-No, no.

00:31:17.930 --> 00:31:19.460
I have a gathering tonight.

00:31:19.590 --> 00:31:21.110
-Don't stand on ceremony.
-No need for formalities. Just sit.

00:31:21.110 --> 00:31:22.130
Try my cooking.

00:31:22.440 --> 00:31:23.510
But I-I came empty-handed.

00:31:23.510 --> 00:31:24.720
I feel a bit embarrassed.

00:31:24.720 --> 00:31:26.110
No need to stand on ceremony.

00:31:26.110 --> 00:31:26.840
We're happy.

00:31:26.930 --> 00:31:28.400
We heard a lot about you from Xia Lei.

00:31:28.400 --> 00:31:29.960
Eight is coming back in a few days
as well,

00:31:29.960 --> 00:31:31.030
along with some other coworkers.

00:31:31.030 --> 00:31:32.310
Now that you've come back as well,

00:31:32.310 --> 00:31:33.790
this is definitely going to work out.

00:31:33.790 --> 00:31:36.480
Your name is... Fan Weijie, right?

00:31:36.720 --> 00:31:37.510
Just... Just call me Fan.

00:31:37.510 --> 00:31:38.840
-Fan.
-Just call me Fan.

00:31:38.960 --> 00:31:39.750
Here's the thing.

00:31:39.750 --> 00:31:42.880
Our East Chemical Plant
is different from other places.

00:31:42.960 --> 00:31:44.440
We don't force people to drink.

00:31:44.440 --> 00:31:45.380
But we do set examples.

00:31:45.380 --> 00:31:46.180
Set examples?

00:31:46.400 --> 00:31:48.260
I'll set an example for you today.

00:31:48.270 --> 00:31:49.720
I'll drink 3 glasses in a row,

00:31:49.720 --> 00:31:51.720
which is considered
our highest form of etiquette here.

00:31:51.720 --> 00:31:52.790
No, no, no, Uncle, please don't.

00:31:52.790 --> 00:31:53.870
It's fine. Don't worry about it.

00:31:53.870 --> 00:31:54.720
Well, Fan.

00:31:54.790 --> 00:31:56.960
This first glass is to welcome you.

00:31:59.790 --> 00:32:00.120
Here.

00:32:02.400 --> 00:32:03.680
This second glass

00:32:04.440 --> 00:32:05.920
is to thank you.

00:32:06.860 --> 00:32:07.520
Watch this.

00:32:10.790 --> 00:32:12.400
This third glass is

00:32:13.590 --> 00:32:15.480
to welcome you, thank you,

00:32:15.640 --> 00:32:18.680
and to wish the acquisition a success.

00:32:21.070 --> 00:32:23.000
If I'd known, I wouldn't have come.

00:32:24.270 --> 00:32:25.530
I believed you'd come.

00:32:27.310 --> 00:32:28.440
Well, Fan.

00:32:29.310 --> 00:32:30.350
You have no idea.

00:32:30.790 --> 00:32:32.000
Our Xia Lei

00:32:32.200 --> 00:32:33.640
has suffered a lot

00:32:34.680 --> 00:32:36.160
for this bidding process.

00:32:36.310 --> 00:32:37.510
But now it's all good.

00:32:37.640 --> 00:32:39.960
With you old classmates
coming back to help,

00:32:39.960 --> 00:32:41.020
whatever happens,

00:32:41.310 --> 00:32:43.440
you can discuss and solve it together.

00:32:43.960 --> 00:32:46.510
This is great. How I wish someone

00:32:46.750 --> 00:32:48.350
could save our Factory No. 3.

00:32:48.590 --> 00:32:50.350
Absolutely. Since we're on this subject,

00:32:50.350 --> 00:32:53.000
on behalf of the old employees

00:32:53.160 --> 00:32:54.200
of Factory No. 3,

00:32:54.200 --> 00:32:55.400
-I'll toast you too.
-Yeah. Right.

00:32:55.400 --> 00:32:56.510
What you're doing is truly...

00:32:56.510 --> 00:32:57.350
Auntie, please don't... Don't...

00:32:57.350 --> 00:32:58.030
There's no need for that.

00:32:58.030 --> 00:32:59.660
It's fine. No worries. Come on.

00:32:59.660 --> 00:33:00.400
She can hold her liquor too.

00:33:00.400 --> 00:33:01.060
No, really.

00:33:01.480 --> 00:33:02.880
Just drink as you please.

00:33:03.200 --> 00:33:04.890
Well, Uncle, Auntie,

00:33:04.920 --> 00:33:06.110
actually, Xia Lei asked me to come here

00:33:06.110 --> 00:33:07.790
to check out something today.

00:33:07.790 --> 00:33:08.960
I didn't know you would be here.

00:33:08.960 --> 00:33:11.000
We'll go through the stuff first,
then eat.

00:33:11.000 --> 00:33:11.750
Business first.

00:33:11.750 --> 00:33:13.000
Okay, you guys
go ahead with your business.

00:33:13.000 --> 00:33:13.830
Go ahead with your business.

00:33:13.830 --> 00:33:14.750
Yes, yes. You guys eat first.

00:33:14.750 --> 00:33:15.550
No need to wait for us.

00:33:15.550 --> 00:33:16.400
No rush.

00:33:16.400 --> 00:33:16.830
Take it easy with the drink, Uncle.

00:33:16.830 --> 00:33:17.590
You go about your business.

00:33:17.590 --> 00:33:18.250
Okay, okay.

00:33:26.720 --> 00:33:28.050
What do you mean by that?

00:33:28.750 --> 00:33:30.750
Bringing your mom and dad into this?

00:33:32.000 --> 00:33:33.920
I didn't expect them to do this either.

00:33:33.920 --> 00:33:35.350
They must have misunderstood.

00:33:35.350 --> 00:33:37.210
How can I control what they think?

00:33:37.270 --> 00:33:39.160
Playing the emotional card with me, huh?

00:33:39.160 --> 00:33:41.550
I told you, Factory No. 3 is
too small a bargaining chip.

00:33:41.550 --> 00:33:43.080
I won't do the acquisition.

00:33:50.030 --> 00:33:50.760
What is this?

00:33:51.100 --> 00:33:51.650
An IOU?

00:33:51.680 --> 00:33:53.210
This is my bargaining chip.

00:33:55.080 --> 00:33:57.170
[Reboot Plan of Factory No. 3 of
East Integrated Chemical Plant]

00:34:02.140 --> 00:34:03.540
[Deputy Director:
Fan Weijie (Sharehholder)]

00:34:04.000 --> 00:34:06.550
This shareholder section...
Why did you put my name here?

00:34:06.550 --> 00:34:07.550
Did I agree?

00:34:07.880 --> 00:34:10.110
I also had shares
at Jiangnan Machinery Plant.

00:34:10.110 --> 00:34:11.170
Did I agree to that?

00:34:12.320 --> 00:34:13.670
Didn't I offer to write you
an IOU

00:34:13.670 --> 00:34:15.679
and a shareholding agreement?
But you refused.

00:34:15.679 --> 00:34:16.710
Now you're pulling this on me?

00:34:16.710 --> 00:34:17.630
The timing wasn't right then.

00:34:17.630 --> 00:34:18.760
Now it is.

00:34:26.070 --> 00:34:28.590
Why is your top business choice
in the Pearl River Delta

00:34:28.590 --> 00:34:30.590
instead of the Yangtze River Delta?

00:34:31.030 --> 00:34:32.340
Because of the climate.

00:34:32.340 --> 00:34:34.400
Lithium batteries are widely used

00:34:34.400 --> 00:34:36.199
in the Pearl River Delta region.

00:34:37.480 --> 00:34:38.030
Besides,

00:34:38.960 --> 00:34:39.880
the new energy industry

00:34:39.880 --> 00:34:41.550
receives huge support there.

00:34:42.630 --> 00:34:44.690
The market prospects are excellent.

00:34:45.190 --> 00:34:46.250
Look further back.

00:34:46.840 --> 00:34:48.110
There's a very detailed research report.

00:34:48.110 --> 00:34:49.710
Wait, why should I read this?

00:34:50.230 --> 00:34:51.000
I thought you hated

00:34:51.000 --> 00:34:52.400
talking feelings when talking money

00:34:52.400 --> 00:34:54.199
or talking money when talking feelings.

00:34:54.199 --> 00:34:55.920
S-So why are you mixing them up now?

00:34:55.920 --> 00:34:57.860
It doesn't matter how you interpret it.

00:34:57.860 --> 00:34:59.860
But you can see my sincerity.

00:34:59.920 --> 00:35:01.400
Everything you want is in there.

00:35:01.400 --> 00:35:02.400
T-Take a look.

00:35:03.550 --> 00:35:04.670
Don't work on an empty stomach.

00:35:04.670 --> 00:35:05.480
Let's eat first,

00:35:05.480 --> 00:35:07.080
then you can get down to work.

00:35:10.420 --> 00:35:11.450
Coming, Auntie.

00:35:18.130 --> 00:35:18.940
Where is it?

00:35:19.630 --> 00:35:20.360
Mr. Yu.

00:35:20.590 --> 00:35:23.150
-Mr. Song.
-You are the first one here.

00:35:23.320 --> 00:35:25.380
Welcome. Come on, please have a seat.

00:35:26.070 --> 00:35:27.110
I might

00:35:28.060 --> 00:35:29.390
be the only one.

00:35:32.800 --> 00:35:34.440
Let me adjust this for you.

00:35:36.090 --> 00:35:36.740
Like this.

00:35:40.130 --> 00:35:41.530
-Please sit.
-Thank you.

00:35:45.670 --> 00:35:46.480
Mr. Song.

00:35:48.190 --> 00:35:49.590
Here's our bid proposal.

00:35:50.960 --> 00:35:52.000
I think

00:35:52.960 --> 00:35:54.030
this tender meeting today

00:35:54.030 --> 00:35:55.800
is actually just a formality.

00:35:56.680 --> 00:35:58.880
I don't see much point in it.

00:35:58.900 --> 00:36:00.500
Why don't we just call it off?

00:36:01.590 --> 00:36:02.400
Mr. Yu, look.

00:36:02.400 --> 00:36:05.230
We must respect the order of this meeting,

00:36:05.350 --> 00:36:05.800
right?

00:36:05.900 --> 00:36:09.050
The deadline for receiving bid proposals
is 12 o'clock.

00:36:10.400 --> 00:36:10.920
Mr. Yu,

00:36:11.150 --> 00:36:12.670
since your bid proposal
has been delivered,

00:36:12.670 --> 00:36:13.510
you may go back now.

00:36:13.510 --> 00:36:14.840
I'm in no hurry.

00:36:14.840 --> 00:36:16.480
I have plenty of time today.

00:36:17.240 --> 00:36:19.720
I'll wait until 12 o'clock to see

00:36:20.280 --> 00:36:21.590
who else shows up.

00:36:25.110 --> 00:36:26.170
Alright, alright.

00:36:26.790 --> 00:36:27.720
You may step out.

00:36:27.970 --> 00:36:28.450
Okay.

00:36:34.550 --> 00:36:35.480
Listen, Song.

00:36:36.550 --> 00:36:39.070
It's only 27 minutes to 12 o'clock.

00:36:40.000 --> 00:36:42.050
Is anyone else coming
to submit a bid proposal?

00:36:42.050 --> 00:36:44.090
Then I'm the only one now, right?

00:36:44.920 --> 00:36:46.320
As for Xia Lei himself,

00:36:47.230 --> 00:36:49.030
I don't think he dares to show up.

00:36:50.730 --> 00:36:51.730
What do you think?

00:36:53.840 --> 00:36:57.150
Zhigang, today is the deadline
for submitting the bid proposal.

00:36:57.150 --> 00:36:59.480
You're restricting my personal freedom,

00:37:00.280 --> 00:37:01.280
which is illegal.

00:37:01.830 --> 00:37:02.760
Do you know that?

00:37:03.150 --> 00:37:04.800
Don't try to scare me, Xia Lei.

00:37:04.800 --> 00:37:06.330
This is a business dispute.

00:37:06.630 --> 00:37:07.670
And I'm talking to you nicely.

00:37:07.670 --> 00:37:09.470
I haven't done anything, right?

00:37:09.510 --> 00:37:10.770
As soon as it's past 12—

00:37:12.620 --> 00:37:14.110
actually it doesn't have to be that late,

00:37:14.110 --> 00:37:16.440
and I'll let you go.

00:37:17.380 --> 00:37:20.440
Besides, such a short time
doesn't constitute a crime.

00:37:23.660 --> 00:37:25.390
Can I use the bathroom?

00:37:26.440 --> 00:37:26.970
Go ahead.

00:37:39.670 --> 00:37:40.230
Don't move!

00:37:40.230 --> 00:37:41.490
Help! Someone help me!

00:37:41.710 --> 00:37:43.480
Help! Help!

00:37:43.920 --> 00:37:44.590
Help!

00:37:46.000 --> 00:37:46.590
Let go!

00:37:49.880 --> 00:37:50.630
Mr. Song.

00:37:51.110 --> 00:37:53.110
I'm Meng Ge, representing Fenlier.

00:37:53.960 --> 00:37:55.090
Please, have a seat.

00:38:07.630 --> 00:38:11.470
You people at Fenlier
really don't know when to give up.

00:38:12.000 --> 00:38:13.400
Xia Lei may have left,

00:38:13.880 --> 00:38:16.260
but he's not the only one at Fenlier.

00:38:20.550 --> 00:38:22.610
Pull over. That's about right. Here.

00:38:22.840 --> 00:38:23.900
What's wrong, bro?

00:38:24.070 --> 00:38:24.600
Xiaoman.

00:38:25.030 --> 00:38:26.800
I've asked around.
He's on the ninth floor.

00:38:26.800 --> 00:38:28.000
-Upstairs, right?
-You four, keep watch.

00:38:28.000 --> 00:38:29.480
-Let's go.
-Let's go.

00:38:29.480 --> 00:38:30.540
Hurry up. Hurry up.

00:38:30.590 --> 00:38:32.650
They're dying of anxiety over there.

00:38:33.630 --> 00:38:34.670
Hurry up. Hurry up.

00:38:34.670 --> 00:38:35.230
There! Over there!

00:38:35.230 --> 00:38:36.000
Ahead! There's a fire! Hurry!

00:38:36.000 --> 00:38:36.960
Quick! Ahead! Ahead!

00:38:36.960 --> 00:38:38.070
Go that way! That way!

00:38:38.070 --> 00:38:39.280
There's a fire! Move, move!

00:38:39.280 --> 00:38:40.360
-Coming!
-Right.

00:38:40.760 --> 00:38:41.440
Go that way!

00:38:41.670 --> 00:38:42.960
-Fire escape on the right!
-Young man.

00:38:42.960 --> 00:38:44.150
Hurry! Go!

00:38:44.280 --> 00:38:45.070
Quick! Quick!

00:38:45.070 --> 00:38:46.130
Hurry up. Hurry up.

00:38:50.360 --> 00:38:51.960
My god. Will this thing work?

00:38:52.000 --> 00:38:52.760
Don't...

00:38:52.760 --> 00:38:53.920
No, wait... This...

00:38:53.920 --> 00:38:55.250
This is a bit dangerous.

00:38:55.760 --> 00:38:57.000
Hello? There's a fire!

00:38:57.000 --> 00:38:57.920
Get out now!

00:38:58.920 --> 00:39:00.180
Hello? There's a fire!

00:39:02.360 --> 00:39:04.040
It's already 11:55.

00:39:04.060 --> 00:39:05.190
Only 5 minutes left.

00:39:05.190 --> 00:39:07.790
Who else will come deliver
their bid proposal?

00:39:10.110 --> 00:39:10.630
Meng Ge,

00:39:11.210 --> 00:39:13.150
is Fenlier participating or not?

00:39:13.150 --> 00:39:14.610
Give me a straight answer.

00:39:14.670 --> 00:39:16.070
What are you waiting for?

00:39:16.280 --> 00:39:17.610
Who are you waiting for?

00:39:17.670 --> 00:39:20.200
After this talk,
there's only 4 minutes left.

00:39:21.190 --> 00:39:22.400
Do it! Nobody move!

00:39:22.880 --> 00:39:23.540
Squat down!

00:39:23.630 --> 00:39:24.290
Don't move!

00:39:25.920 --> 00:39:27.000
-I'll leave them to you, bro.
-No problem.

00:39:27.000 --> 00:39:29.130
I'll take him over there immediately.

00:39:31.140 --> 00:39:32.770
[Bid Document]

00:39:37.710 --> 00:39:38.440
I made it.

00:39:38.760 --> 00:39:41.020
Mr. Song, here's Xia Lei's bid proposal.

00:39:45.170 --> 00:39:46.700
Why didn't he come himself?

00:39:47.540 --> 00:39:48.870
You'd have to ask Mr. Yu.

00:39:48.960 --> 00:39:49.760
He knows best.

00:39:50.520 --> 00:39:52.730
Ask me? What do I know?

00:39:53.990 --> 00:39:55.520
You're Yu Qiangbei, right?

00:40:16.190 --> 00:40:17.000
I once thought

00:40:17.000 --> 00:40:18.880
I'd never have anything to do
with this place again.

00:40:18.880 --> 00:40:21.010
I didn't expect to come back after all.

00:40:21.070 --> 00:40:23.400
I didn't expect you to come today, either.

00:40:23.840 --> 00:40:24.630
You quit,

00:40:24.630 --> 00:40:26.480
but someone has to take over the project.

00:40:26.480 --> 00:40:27.550
If not me, then who?

00:40:28.490 --> 00:40:31.610
Why didn't you just submit
the bid proposal?

00:40:36.280 --> 00:40:37.000
You guys...

00:40:38.740 --> 00:40:40.800
So something's going on with you two.

00:40:42.410 --> 00:40:44.210
Why do you work with just anyone?

00:40:44.360 --> 00:40:46.020
What's that supposed to mean?

00:40:47.790 --> 00:40:48.800
You'd be scared to death if you knew.

00:40:48.800 --> 00:40:50.800
Don't try to pry into my background.

00:40:50.800 --> 00:40:53.130
Actually, I prepared two plans for today.

00:40:53.480 --> 00:40:54.540
If you hadn't come,

00:40:54.710 --> 00:40:56.710
I'd have submitted the bid proposal
on behalf of Fenlier;

00:40:56.710 --> 00:40:57.890
and now that you've come,

00:40:57.890 --> 00:41:00.090
I'll invest in you on behalf of Fenlier.

00:41:00.920 --> 00:41:02.520
Will Kong Peng agree to this?

00:41:02.630 --> 00:41:05.290
Kong Peng doesn't call the shots
for me anymore.

00:41:07.000 --> 00:41:08.800
I should congratulate you then.

00:41:09.320 --> 00:41:10.380
But I didn't expect

00:41:10.520 --> 00:41:12.850
you could persuade Fan Weijie to help you.

00:41:14.520 --> 00:41:16.440
Before stepping into the meeting room,

00:41:16.440 --> 00:41:18.370
I couldn't be sure he would help me.

00:41:19.560 --> 00:41:20.680
This is my bid proposal

00:41:20.680 --> 00:41:22.100
and the partnership agreement.

00:41:22.100 --> 00:41:23.070
[Bid Document]

00:41:23.070 --> 00:41:24.550
I've already signed them.

00:41:25.710 --> 00:41:26.770
Why give them to me?

00:41:27.070 --> 00:41:28.230
I was thinking, if I

00:41:28.230 --> 00:41:29.430
run into any trouble,

00:41:29.630 --> 00:41:31.550
I hope you can help me submit them.

00:41:32.110 --> 00:41:33.360
If you're willing,

00:41:33.670 --> 00:41:34.760
sign them.

00:41:37.190 --> 00:41:38.390
Why should I help you?

00:41:40.590 --> 00:41:41.590
Because I believe

00:41:42.610 --> 00:41:44.440
that my bid proposal is the best plan

00:41:44.440 --> 00:41:45.960
for the future of Factory No. 3.

00:41:45.960 --> 00:41:48.020
And it's also what Mr. Song hopes for.

00:41:49.150 --> 00:41:50.750
If you neither want to do this

00:41:51.140 --> 00:41:52.430
nor want to quit,

00:41:53.260 --> 00:41:54.920
I'll give you my bid proposal.

00:41:55.440 --> 00:41:57.700
You can fill in whatever amount you want.

00:41:59.550 --> 00:42:01.080
So everything you're doing

00:42:01.260 --> 00:42:02.610
is for Factory No. 3?

00:42:04.510 --> 00:42:05.030
Yes.

00:42:06.670 --> 00:42:08.670
I'm only doing this for our factory.

00:42:09.360 --> 00:42:11.090
Even if you take my bid proposal

00:42:11.490 --> 00:42:13.300
and submit it as your own,

00:42:16.720 --> 00:42:18.050
I'll still be thankful.

00:42:20.190 --> 00:42:21.850
You're really something now.

00:42:22.400 --> 00:42:23.870
Why were you so sure I'd come?

00:42:23.870 --> 00:42:24.960
If I had been sure,

00:42:24.960 --> 00:42:26.960
I wouldn't have run like a dog, okay?

00:42:27.050 --> 00:42:28.650
But I still want to thank you.

00:42:29.030 --> 00:42:29.840
For what?

00:42:30.360 --> 00:42:32.000
I have to pay back what I owe you.

00:42:32.000 --> 00:42:33.660
Besides, you trust me so much.

00:42:33.870 --> 00:42:36.390
So what made you decide to
help me in the end?

00:42:39.920 --> 00:42:41.380
Because you're handsome.

00:42:41.680 --> 00:42:43.150
You're never serious.

00:42:44.510 --> 00:42:45.940
We've evaluated this project.

00:42:45.940 --> 00:42:47.270
It does have potential.

00:42:47.320 --> 00:42:48.710
Otherwise, I wouldn't have persuaded
the new leadership

00:42:48.710 --> 00:42:49.640
to invest in you.

00:42:51.000 --> 00:42:53.000
Invest? Now?

00:42:54.710 --> 00:42:55.590
Yeah, now.

00:42:56.850 --> 00:42:58.150
We've got money!

00:42:58.150 --> 00:42:58.990
You don't say.

00:42:59.480 --> 00:43:01.540
Carry Ms. Meng's bag for her. Come on.

00:43:03.500 --> 00:43:04.140
This is awesome.